Record.CAVI-Lemma: Fragmentary RF cup. Combines Euergidean and Epeleian elements (Beazley). Last quarter sixth. Ca. 510 (Giroux).
Record.CAVI-Subject: Int.: a young warrior running. A: two nude youths leading horses (one turned to left the other to right). B: a young trainer with three nude athletes.
Record.CAVI-Inscriptions: Int.: around the tondo: to right of the head: h[---]. To its left: [---] κα[λος], retr.{1}. A: near the lip: [--- π]αις κ[αλος]. [hο πα]ις καλος{2}. B: near the lip: [h]ο παις [κα]λος.
Record.CAVI-Comments: The foot formerly attached to G 23.
Record.CAVI-Footnotes: {1} no doubt: καλος and h[ο παις]. {2} so CVA: is that right?
Record.AVI-Bibliography: Blösch (1940), 50/under no. 1. — ARV[2] (1963), 104/6 (no bibl.). — H. Giroux, CVA Louvre 19, France 28 (1977), pls. 54,2-3 and 55,1-3; foot profile p. 32. — Add.[2] (1989), 172.

Record.CAVI-Inscriptions: Nonsense: A: between the duelist's legs: υοσνον. B: between legs of the third and fourth males: χσ/ρ(κ)[ο{3}. Between the backs of the fifth and sixth males: κσδο(.)(σ){4}.
Record.CAVI-Footnotes: {1} too early? {2} listed as a fragmentary BF column krater. {3} perhaps not complete fore, as there is a trace of a letter higher up. {4} read as retr., but the reading is uncertain.
Record.AVI-Bibliography: J. Paul Getty Museum (1983), 72/58 (not ill.){2}. — A.J. Clark, CVA Malibu 1, USA 23 (1988), pls. 50,1-2 and 51,1-2 (no bibl.).

Record.CAVI-Lemma: Frs. of BF column krater. Lydos. Third quarter sixth. 550-540 (Kossatz-Deissmann).
Record.CAVI-Inscriptions: A: around a maenad's head: Φιλοποσ(ο̅)(?){1}. To left of the face of a satyr playing the flutes: Μολπαιος, retr. To right of Hephaestus' head: hεφαιστος. Below this inscription, lined up with the preceding on the right: ονος. Under the ithyphallic donkey and above a prostrate satyr, curved around the donkey's penis: Ουκαλεγον{2}. By a satyr who is carrying an amphora: Εοι[--]{3}. By the lower leg of a satyr: h[ε]ρμοθαλες{4}. Below another satyr: Κραται[--]{5}. Between a pair of feet: [--]πισιος{6}.
Record.CAVI-Comments: Loan. At least 12 frs., not yet put together. The word ονος occurs with a rider also on a Corinthian amphora, Berlin 1652, Lorber (1979), no. 88, pl. 19.
Record.CAVI-Footnotes: {1} so K.-D.; the last letter is quite uncertain; φιλοποσια occurs in Xen. {2} known as an old man `who does not care' in Il. 3.148; cf. also Cab. Méd. 851. {3} from ἠοῖος(?) (G. Neumann). {3} or hερμοθαλες [[h(ε)]], syllabic? {5} Κραται[ος] or Κραται[μενες] or the like (K.-D. or Neumann?). {6} if pi is an error for rho: Charisios? No name known to me ends in --]pisios.
